⭐ STEP 1 — Create a folder for Kubernetes files

mkdir mini
cd mini

Go inside → create a file named:
code.
mysql-deployment.yml

Paste this into it:

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: mysql
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: mysql
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: mysql
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: mysql
        image: mysql:5.7
        env:
        - name: MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD
          value: "password"
        ports:
        - containerPort: 3306


This creates one MySQL pod.

⭐ STEP 2 — Apply it to Kubernetes

Open CMD inside that folder
(type cmd in the folder’s address bar)

Run:
kubectl apply -f mysql-deployment.yml

Check if pod is running:

kubectl get pods

You should see:

mysql-xxxxxxxxx   1/1   Running

⭐ STEP 3 — SCALE THE MYSQL DEPLOYMENT

Scale to 3 replicas:

kubectl scale deployment mysql --replicas=3

Check:

kubectl get pods

You will now see:

mysql-xxxxx   Running  
mysql-yyyyy   Running  
mysql-zzzzz   Running  
